column5: bIGFISH You going to Quinte this year? We are up the 11th for aa week. Staying at merland. Atlanta Dave
Can't make it this year, Dave. Just had surgery. The bite is going very well. SuperDad is the PREMIER guy for Quinte info. Send him a note...he'll help you out.

Quinte is on fire. I took my dad this weekend for two days of sticking monsters and we did. Saturday we broke the 30" mark twice and Sunday we broke 30" seven or eight times times. We did get one totally deformed fish just over 27" and weighing 11pounds 14 ounces! The big dogs are rolling in now and it's only going to get better. Nice eaters are few and far between though so if you're out for a meat hunt it's out of the question. Keep the cameras handy.

spent the week of the 20 to 26 at quintee fishing was good boated 39 fish. 20 fish over 10 pounds 5 fish between 12 and 13 pounds and fishing will get better everyday till ice up. if you have the opertunity go you won't be sorry. mallard1
Anyone know recent news on the bite at Quinte?
I have heard October and November are the time of the year to catch the big ones,however, I've never been there and haven't seen a report. Steve

Lets just say they are on the feed. Hitting anything you throw at them. The weekend produced many personel best for a lot of people.
Lets just say they are on the feed. Hitting anything you throw at them. The weekend produced many personel best for a lot of people.

The fishing has been sporatic, some doing REAL well and others not doing anything. A couple of walleye pros were fishing last week and had double and triple headers with 12 lb fish. There were right on the spot. We fished the same day about four miles from them and got skunked. The Big mama's are getting close and it's the time of the year - hopefully we'll get some of the action. Stay Tuned or go to www.quintefishing.com (discussion board) David Delcloo aka Superdad
